The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | China spy
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                      China spy
                            
	Itanagar, May 24: A man found loitering at a ferry ghat in Lohit district of Arunachal Pradesh has been arrested on the suspicion of being a Chinese spy.        
	Deputy superintendent of police Manik Gogoi today said: On May 18, local fishermen told police they had seen Guan Liang, 28, loitering suspiciously at a ferry ghat. We suspect him to be a Chinese spy. When the police demanded Guans passport, the youth said his name was Guan Liang from Henan, China. In English, he said he was the manager of a Beijing restaurant.         
	The police said Guan told them he had a map of India and Chinese currency that he destroyed while sneaking in.                                                                                                                                                           
